procedures.name: Blood Draw
procedures.label: Blood Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), HIV, hepatitis B and C screening, and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour pooled collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full or symptom-driven physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of heart's electrical activity using a triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate and intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc).

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Oral Administration of Study Intervention
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water after an overnight fast.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Intravenous Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Detection, collection, and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements, including recording time and weight of fecal samples.

procedures.name: Clinical Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Lab Tests
procedures.description: Analysis of blood and urine samples, including serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and urinalysis.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws. To be flushed a minimum of every 8 hours and not left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device used for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
